=begin pod
=head2 get-font

B<Note: The native version of this routine is deprecated in gtk4-lib() since version 4.10>

Gets the currently-selected font name.

Note that this can be a different string than what you set with
L<.set-font()|#set-font>, as the font chooser widget may
normalize font names and thus return a string with a different
structure. For example, “Helvetica Italic Bold 12” could be
normalized to “Helvetica Bold Italic 12”.

Use L<.equal() in class FontDescription|/content-docs/api2/reference/Pango/FontDescription#equal> if you want to compare two
font descriptions.

=begin code
method get-font (--> Str )
=end code

Return value; A string with the name
  of the current font. 

